Dear Homeowner,

This letter serves as official notice of a real estate tax adjustment applied to your primary residence at 42 Longwood Terrace, Brookline, MA 02445 (Parcel ID BRK-2027-04412) for Fiscal Year 2027.

Following review of the Owner-Occupied Senior Credit application submitted on June 24, 2026 in the name of your co-resident and household member Jung-hee Lee (DOB 1958-06-12), and following verification that Ms. Lee is on title as a joint owner with the deed executed October 4, 2023, Ms. Lee has been approved under the Senior Owner-Occupied Credit provision (M.G.L. c. 59 s. 5, Clause 41C variant). The approved credit is $150.00 per quarterly installment.

The credit is effective retroactively from the beginning of Fiscal Year 2027 (Q1). Prior-quarter overpayments (Q1, Q2, Q3) have already been applied as a rolling credit against the current outstanding balance, so no Q1-Q3 refund is issued.

The credit applies to your Q4 installment, reducing the amount payable accordingly. Payment due date remains November 30, 2026. Payment methods remain unchanged (see the Q4 statement mailed August 3, 2026 for portal and mailing details).

This adjustment does not modify the assessed value of the property or the annualized tax rate. It applies only to the amount payable per installment. The credit will renew automatically for FY 2028 provided Ms. Lee's residency status is unchanged; a reapplication may be required if a household change occurs.

If you have questions about eligibility or wish to appeal the credit determination, please contact the Norfolk County Assessor's Office at 781-461-6104.

